Dante (Silvio Guindane) is the favorite son of Nicolau (Stepan Nercessian), owner of a chop shop in the city of Rio de Janeiro. Quinho (Ãƒâ€šngelo Paes Leme) has always been jealous of his father's predilection for his foster brother and forges his own kidnapping in order to extort the father. Dante mobilizes himself aiming to rescue the brother, however he finds out the simulation before being arrested.

Seven years later, Dante is back home when he notices that his wife Luana (Aline Fanju) is married with Quinho and that everything in home and in family business is now completely different. These facts awaken his thirst after revenge against those that have prejudiced his life.
